definition: car/vehicle/CL:輛|辆[liang4]/machine/to shape with a lathe/Kangxi radical 159
enclosed carriage for carrying passengers/motor carriage/car or bus/limousine/CL:部[bu4],輛|辆[liang4]

sentences.english: This essay comes from a coupe reverse engineering project.
sentences.chinese: 本课题来源于某轿跑车逆向设计项目。

sentences.english: This is the Chery A6 coupe, spied testing in the UK.
sentences.chinese: 这是奇瑞的A6轿跑车，在英国做秘密测试。

sentences.english: A team member shall start the Traveller Robot for boarding onto the Kago by a single switch operation.
sentences.chinese: 一位队员应通过单一开关开启旅行机器人上轿。

sentences.english: Thin bamboo and the half summer heel set out together later car Jiao.
sentences.chinese: 淡竹与半夏跟在车轿后，一起出发。

sentences.english: Goodfellas, Lexus coupe, there are now free to buy.
sentences.chinese: 好家伙，雷克萨斯轿跑车，现在有钱买闲地。

sentences.english: This one weighed two tons plus and was more than 19 feet long.
sentences.chinese: 这款轿跑重达两吨多，长度超过19英尺。

sentences.english: The Kago may touch the floor of the Kago Zone for the purpose of boarding.
sentences.chinese: 为完成上轿，轿子在旅馆区域可触地。

sentences.english: But before they became extinct, big coupes were kings of the automotive jungle.
sentences.chinese: 在彻底绝迹之前，大型双门轿跑一直是车市的王者。

sentences.english: Its curvaceous body is topped by a coupe-like roofline.
sentences.chinese: 其婀娜多姿的身体首位的是一轿跑车般的车顶。

sentences.english: Pozi who has been behind all of the palanquin, to catch up.
sentences.chinese: 后面的婆子们已都下了轿，赶上前来。

sentences.english: The Kago may touch the floor of the Kago Zone when the Traveller Robot alights from the Kago.
sentences.chinese: 当旅行机器人下轿时，轿子可以在轿子区触地。

sentences.english: He woke alone, and found the litter halted.
sentences.chinese: 他独自醒来，发现业已落轿。

sentences.english: We were going to travel together to Paris.
sentences.chinese: 恍夕丰轿莶计奉袭斧陋我们曾打算一起去巴黎旅游。

sentences.english: King Solomon made himself a chariot of the wood of Lebanon.
sentences.chinese: 所罗门王用黎巴嫩木，为自己制造一乘华轿。

sentences.english: King Solomon made himself a chariot of the wood of lebanon.
sentences.chinese: 所罗门王用利巴嫩木，为自己制造一乘华轿。
